Package: rsalad
Title: A mix of useful R functions that are good for you
Version: 0.0.2.0
Authors@R: "Dean Attali <daattali@gmail.com> [aut, cre]"
Description: Collection of functions that help with easily manipulating
    data.frames (e.g.converting variables to factors, rearranging variables),
    improving ggplot2 plots (e.g. removing certain gridlines, rotating axis
    labels), and improve usability and functionality of knitr::spin (e.g. better
    handling of working directories and output directories).
URL: https://github.com/daattali/rsalad
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0.2)
Imports:
    dplyr (>= 0.3.0),
    magrittr (>= 1.5)
Suggests:
    ggplot2 (>= 1.0.0),
    knitr (>= 1.7),
    lazyeval (>= 0.1.9),
    markdown (>= 0.7),
    microbenchmark (>= 1.4),
    nycflights13 (>= 0.1),
    R.utils (>= 1.34.0),
    testthat (>= 0.9.1)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
VignetteBuilder: knitr
